---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — SFCE Learning App"
  description="Privacy policy for the SFCE Learning native app for iPhone, iPad, and Mac."
  canonicalPath="/app/privacy-policy/"
  footerVariant="app"
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 sm:py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary dark:text-dark-text-secondary mb-8">
      <strong class="text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary">Last updated:</strong> May 8, 2026
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-8 text-text-secondary dark:text-dark-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        SFCE Learning app ("the app", "we", "us") is a native study guide for the Symfony Framework
        Certification Exam. This Privacy Policy explains what information the app uses, where it is
        stored, and how privacy-related Apple services are used.
      </p>

      <p>
        SFCE Learning app is designed to work offline for its core study content. The app does not
        require an account with us, does not use advertising, does not use analytics SDKs, and does
        not track you across apps or websites.
      </p>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Information We Do Not Collect</h2>
        <p>
          We do not collect, sell, rent, or share personal information for advertising or tracking.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">SFCE Learning app does not collect:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>Your name, email address, phone number, or address</li>
          <li>Precise or coarse location</li>
          <li>Contacts, photos, camera, microphone, or health data</li>
          <li>Advertising identifiers</li>
          <li>Analytics events or telemetry</li>
          <li>Crash reports sent to our own servers</li>
          <li>Browsing history from the in-app browser</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The app does not include third-party analytics, advertising SDKs, or social tracking SDKs.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Study Progress</h2>
        <p>
          SFCE Learning app stores your study progress so the app can show completed references,
          progress indicators, and your last-read location.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">This information may include:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>Symfony version selected for study progress</li>
          <li>Completed reference identifiers</li>
          <li>Completion timestamps stored locally by the app</li>
          <li>Last-read topic and chapter identifiers</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          This data is stored on your device using Apple system storage technologies such as
          SwiftData and UserDefaults. It is used only to provide app functionality.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">iCloud Sync</h2>
        <p>
          If iCloud is available for your Apple Account and enabled on your device, SFCE Learning
          app syncs completed reference identifiers through Apple's iCloud key-value storage so your
          progress can appear on your other Apple devices.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The synced data is limited to completion state by Symfony version and reference identifier.
          SFCE Learning app does not sync your name, email address, or other contact information.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          iCloud sync is provided by Apple. We do not operate a server for this data and do not have
          access to the contents of your iCloud account. You can manage iCloud access for apps in
          your device system settings.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Calendar Integration</h2>
        <p>
          SFCE Learning app can create study sessions in your calendar when you choose the "Add to
          Calendar" action.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          When you use this feature, the app asks for calendar permission through Apple's system
          permission prompt. The app requests write-only calendar access where supported. Calendar
          events created by SFCE Learning app may include:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>A study title based on the selected chapter or reference</li>
          <li>A suggested start and end time</li>
          <li>Reference links or notes when relevant</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          SFCE Learning app uses calendar access only to create the events you request. The app does
          not upload your calendar data to us.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Reminders Integration</h2>
        <p>
          SFCE Learning app can create study reminders when you choose the "Add Reminder" action.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          When you use this feature, the app asks for reminders permission through Apple's system
          permission prompt. Reminders created by SFCE Learning app may include:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>A study reminder title based on the selected chapter or reference</li>
          <li>Notes or reference links when relevant</li>
          <li>A due date if you choose one in the reminder editor</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          SFCE Learning app uses reminders access only to create reminders you request. The app does
          not upload your reminders data to us.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">In-App Browser and External Reference Links</h2>
        <p>
          SFCE Learning app includes reference links to external documentation and websites. When
          you open a reference link, the page may open in an in-app browser or in your system
          browser.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          External websites are not operated by SFCE Learning app. Those websites may receive
          standard web request information, such as your IP address, browser information, cookies,
          or other data depending on their own privacy practices. Their handling of data is governed
          by their own privacy policies.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          SFCE Learning app does not collect or store your in-app browsing history.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Purchases</h2>
        <p>
          If the app offers a purchase, such as a quiz unlock, the purchase flow is handled by Apple
          through the App Store and StoreKit.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          SFCE Learning app may check Apple-provided purchase entitlement status to unlock purchased
          functionality. We do not receive or store your payment card details or App Store payment
          information.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Apple's handling of purchase, billing, and Apple Account information is governed by
          Apple's own privacy policy and App Store terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Data Sharing</h2>
        <p>
          We do not sell your data. We do not share your data with advertisers or data brokers.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Data may be processed by Apple services when you use Apple platform features such as
          iCloud, Calendar, Reminders, StoreKit, SafariServices, WebKit, or the App Store. These
          services are provided by Apple and are subject to Apple's privacy practices.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Data Retention and Deletion</h2>
        <p>
          Study progress remains on your device unless you delete it, uninstall the app, or remove
          the app's data through system settings.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          iCloud-synced progress remains in your iCloud account according to Apple's iCloud behavior
          and your iCloud settings. You can manage iCloud data and app access in system settings.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Calendar events and reminders created by SFCE Learning app remain in your Calendar or
          Reminders app until you edit or delete them.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          SFCE Learning app is a professional study tool for developers preparing for a
          certification exam. The app is not directed to children and does not knowingly collect
          personal information from children.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy if the app's privacy practices change. When we make
          changes, we will update the "Last updated" date above.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For privacy questions, contact the developer through the support contact listed on the
          SFCE Learning app's App Store product page or the official project website.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
